Package uk.co.terminological.rjava.types

Class RNamed<X extends RObject>

java.lang.Object
uk.co.terminological.rjava.types.RNamed<X>
Type Parameters:
X - an RObject
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Map.Entry<String,X>, RObject
public class RNamed<X extends RObject> extends Object implements RObject, Map.Entry<String,X>
A named object. R seems to be able to attach names to most things. This is somewhat impractical to implement in java, as it conflicts a bit with the idea of map structures. This class is generally used when converting vector based views of the data (R like) to row based views of the data (java like). This is a work in progress.
Author:
terminological
